This README file contains information on the contents of the meta-castle-gimbal layer.

# meta-castle-gimbal
Yocto Scarthgap layer for a Raspberry Pi 3 based gimbal controller image.

## Target
- Yocto release: scarthgap
- Machine: raspberrypi3
- Distro: castle-gimbal
- Image: castle-gimbal-image

## Hardware
- Raspberry Pi 3B
- MPU-6050 over I2C
- Two BLDC driver control signals over PWM
- USB-to-UART debug console
- Wi-Fi
- Camera over V4L2

## Layer Dependencies
Expected workspace layout:

```text
yocto-rpi/
  poky/
  meta-openembedded/
  meta-raspberrypi/
  meta-castle-gimbal/

Required layers:
poky/meta
poky/meta-poky
poky/meta-yocto-bsp
meta-openembedded/meta-oe
meta-openembedded/meta-python
meta-raspberrypi
meta-castle-gimbal

## Build
From the workspace root:

$ cd ~/yocto-rpi
$ TEMPLATECONF=../meta-castle-gimbal/conf/templates/castle-gimbal source poky/oe-init-build-env build-castle
$ bitbake castle-gimbal-image

## Flash SD Card
Check the SD card device carefully:

$ lsblk

Example for /dev/sdX:
$ bzcat tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/castle-gimbal-image-raspberrypi3.rootfs.wic.bz2 | sudo dd of=/dev/sdX bs=4M conv=fsync status=progress
$ sync

[ --- Board checklist --- ]
## Verified Interfaces
I2C:
root# ls /dev/i2c*
root# i2cdetect -y 1
Expected MPU-6050 address:
0x68

PWM:
root# ls /sys/class/pwm
pwmchip0
root# cat /sys/class/pwm/pwmchip0/npwm
2

Camera:
root# v4l2-ctl -d /dev/video0 --list-formats-ext
root# v4l2-ctl -d /dev/video0 \
  --set-fmt-video=width=640,height=480,pixelformat=MJPG \
  --stream-mmap \
  --stream-count=1 \
  --stream-to=/tmp/capture.mjpg

Wi-Fi:
root# ip link set wlan0 up
root# iw dev wlan0 scan | grep SSID

## Notes
- The image enables I2C for the MPU-6050.
- The image enables two PWM channels using dtoverlay=pwm-2chan.
- The pwm-2chan.dtbo overlay is included in the boot partition through RPI_KERNEL_DEVICETREE_OVERLAYS.
- The image includes v4l-utils, i2c-tools, iw, and wpa-supplicant for hardware validation.
- Application code for motor control, recording, and video streaming will be added later.
